text.section:
A grantor is not required to comply with the provisions of this section if the reason for the cancellation or nonrenewal includes any of the following:
For any items that are not in dispute, the failure of the distributor to pay the grantor for commercial goods received;
The actual or pending insolvency, the occurrence of an assignment for the benefit of creditors, or the bankruptcy of the distributor or of its parent entity or of any affiliated entity that has financial control over it;
A danger to the public health or safety caused by the distributor or any affiliated entity over which it has control;
Abandonment of the agreement by the distributor or any other matter which a court finds to be justification for a premature cancellation or nonrenewal;
Conduct by the distributor expressly prohibited under a written agreement that materially affects the relationship between the distributor and grantor;
Conduct by the distributor that materially alters the commercial viability of the grantor's commercial goods in the marketplace; or
Affirmative bad faith, dishonest, fraudulent, or illegal acts by the distributor.
